						<element name="Draconic Link To Magic" type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_DLTM">
							<description>
								<p>Characters that choose this archetype change their spell casting abilities from a half caster to a full caster and follow the chart below for spell casting. Additionally, you gain The Subtly of Dragon Magic Feature. </p>
							</description>
							<sheet>
								<description>Characters that choose this archetype change their spell casting abilities from a half caster to a full caster and follow the chart below for spell casting. Additionally, you gain The Subtly of Dragon Magic Feature. </description>
							</sheet>
						</element>

						<element name="Subtly of Dragon Magic" type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_SODM">
							<description>
								<p>When you are recording spells into your spell book Wizard spells do not cost gold and non-wizard spells take only 1 hour per level. Furthermore, when you cast a spell in the True Language, you can choose to cast it without material or verbal components. </p>
							</description>
							<sheet>
								<description>When you are recording spells into your spell book Wizard spells do not cost gold and non-wizard spells take only 1 hour per level. Furthermore, when you cast a spell in the True Language, you can choose to cast it without material or verbal components. </description>
							</sheet>
						
						</element>

						<element name="Ancient Language casting" type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_AncientLanguageCasting">
							<description>
								<p>At 3rd Level you unlock the ability to cast spells in ancient language. With the ancient language a rider can cast a spell he would normally expend a slot for without using the slot.</p>
								<p class="indent">To cast in this language the rider must know the correct words to use it and the spell must be recorded in his spellbook.</p>
								<p class="indent">The dragon rider learns (3 + your intelligence modifier) words from the ancient language which self-translate in Spellbook of The Dragon Riders.</p>
								<p class="indent">o further learn words from the ancient language books it takes 1 week per word to decipher. (A suggested downtime activity)</p>
							</description>
						</element>

						<element name="Telepathy read thoughts " type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_TPR">
							<description>
								<p>t 6th level the rider gets a passive sense of how every living creature feels towards the rider within 10 feet.</p>
								<p class="indent">Additionally, as an action the rider may try to read a person's thoughts within 60 feet of you. The creature must make a wisdom saving throw. If the creature succeeds on the saving throw, you can’t use this feature on it again until you finish a long rest.</p>
								<p class="indent">If the creature fails its save, you can read its surface thoughts (those foremost in its mind, reflecting its current emotions and what it is actively thinking about) when it is within 60 feet of you. This effect lasts for 1 minute. </p>
                            </description>
							<sheet>
							<description>the rider gets a passive sense of how every living creature feels towards the rider within 10 feet. Also, as an action the rider may try to read a person's thoughts within 60 feet of you. The creature must make a wisdom saving throw. If the creature succeeds on the saving throw, you can’t use this feature on it again until you finish a long rest. If the creature fails its save, you can read its surface thoughts (those foremost in its mind, reflecting its current emotions and what it is actively thinking about) when it is within 60 feet of you. </description>
							</sheet>
						</element>

						<element name="Over Exertion Cast " type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_OVEREC">
							<description>
								<p>At 9th Level The Rider may cast any spell in their spellbook regardless of spell slot level. </p>
								<p class="indent"> The Spell can only be cast in the ancient language. A Spell 1 level higher than the Magus possible cast will add 1 level of exhaustion. A spell up to 2 levels higher than the Riders possible cast will render the caster unconscious. If the spell is 3 or more levels higher than the caster can expend it will kill the caster after resolved. </p>
                        	</description>
							<sheet>
								<description>The Rider may cast any spell in their spellbook regardless of spell slot level.The Spell can only be cast in the ancient language. A Spell 1 level higher than the Magus possible cast will add 1 level of exhaustion. A spell up to 2 levels higher than the Riders possible cast will render the caster unconscious. If the spell is 3 or more levels higher than the caster can expend it will kill the caster after resolved. </description>
							</sheet>
						</element>

						<element name="Wrath of the Dragon" type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_WrathofTheDragon">
							<description>
								<p>Starting at level 11th, when your enemy/enemies rolls a dexterity saving throw, you may subtract 1d4 + your charisma modifier from their roll. You may do this 3 times per long rest. </p>
							</description>
							<sheet>
								<description> When your enemy/enemies rolls a dexterity saving throw, you may subtract 1d4 + your charisma modifier from their roll. You may do this 3 times per long rest. </description>
							</sheet>
						</element>

						<element name="Draconic Soul " type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_DraconicSoul">
							<description>
								<p>Starting at 15th Level, once per long rest, when a Magus who sought power falls in battle, they will see a flash of color in the darkness surrounding them, and a voice commanding them to rise and ensure the destruction of their enemies will run through their head. </p>
								<p class="indent"> Upon reaching zero hit-points and falling unconscious, there will be an explosion of elemental energy in a 20-foot radius centered around the unconscious scholar, dealing 6d6 elemental damage of their dragon’s affiliated type to all creatures within the radius. </p>

                            </description>
							<sheet>
								<description>Once on each of your turns when you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can cause the attack to deal an extra 1d8 damage type on the Dragon Domain table to the target. When you reach 14th level, the extra damage increases to 2d8.</description>
							</sheet>
						</element>

						<element name="Full Dragon Cast " type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_Magus_FullDragonCast">
							<description>
								<p>Starting at 18th level your bond with your dragon is so strong it can be felt through the weave. When you cast a spell using the ancient language you may choose to add your dragon partner’s intelligence modifier to your spell attack roll or spell dc and damage rolls. </p>
                                <p class="indent"> This feature can be used a number of times equal to your intelligence modifier a minimum of 1 per long rest.  </p>
							</description>
							<sheet>
								<description> When you cast a spell using the ancient language you may choose to add your dragon partner’s intelligence modifier to your spell attack roll or spell dc and damage rolls. This feature can be used a number of times equal to your intelligence modifier a minimum of 1 per long rest.  </description>
							</sheet>
						</element>


								<element name="Full Casting" type="Archetype Feature" source="Dragon Riders of Abeir" id="ID_MYHB_DR_ARCHETYPE_FEATURE_FULLCAST_SPELLCASTING">
									<description>
										<p>When you reach 3rd level, you augment your Arcane prowess with the ability to cast more powerful spells.</p>
										<p class="indent">
											<strong>
												<em>Spell Slots.</em>
											</strong> The Nomad Spellcasting table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your spells of 1st level and higher. To cast one of these spells, you must expend a slot of the spell’s level or higher. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.</p>
										<p class="indent">For example, if you know the 1st-level spell shield and have a 1st-level and a 2nd-level spell slot available, you can cast shield using either slot.</p>

